After the success of Right Hand, this duo returns with a powerful musical face-off. Packed with bold lyrics and a bass-heavy beat by Desi Crew, Pecha is designed for loud speakers and dance floors. Whether you're cruising in your car or at a party, this vibe is infectious!

snippet.title: Lee Cronin‚Äôs The Mummy | Official Teaser
snippet.description:
Some things are meant to stay buried. #LeeCroninsTheMummy only in theaters April 17, 2026.

Hot off the record-setting resurrection of EVIL DEAD RISE, writer/director Lee Cronin turns to one of the most iconic horror stories of all time with an audacious and twisted retelling: LEE CRONIN‚ÄôS THE MUMMY. 

The young daughter of a journalist disappears into the desert without a trace‚Äîeight years later, the broken family is shocked when she is returned to them, as what should be a joyful reunion turns into a living nightmare.

The film stars Jack Reynor, Laia Costa, May Calamawy, Natalie Grace, with Veronica Falc√≥n. The film is written and directed by Cronin, and produced by James Wan, Jason Blum and John Keville. The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Macdara Kelleher and Lee Cronin. 

Cronin is supported behind the camera by a team of sterling film artisans, including director of photography Dave Garbett, production designer Nick Bassett, editor Bryan Shaw, costume designer Joanna Eatwell, music by Stephen McKeon and casting by Terri Taylor and Sarah Domeier Lindo. 

New Line Cinema, Atomic Monster and Blumhouse Present, A Wicked/Good Production, A Lee Cronin Film: LEE CRONIN‚ÄôS THE MUMMY. The film will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, only in theaters and IMAXÔÉí in North America on April 17, 2026, and internationally beginning 15 April 2026.

Lyrics:
Dil wohi sukoon dhoonde
Waisa hi qaraar maange 
Dil wohi sukoon dhoonde
Waisa hi qaraar maange 

Jo qudrat ne bikhere the
Bas meri raahon mein
Aur qismat ne sajaaye the
Meri nigaahon mein

Jaane ab kahaan milega 
Kahaan chhupa hoga 
Mil jaata toh rakh leta main
Apni panaahon mein

Woh sukoon shayad mujhse hi hai
Mujh mein hi tha aur mujh mein hi hai

Jhaank loon khud mein zara, sab kuch hai andar mere
Lehron pe milta nahin, jo gehre samandar mile 
Mehsoos hoga mujhe, jab khudko pehchanunga
Dil ke andar dekh kar, apni rooh ko jaanunga

Doobega‚Ä¶ Doobega‚Ä¶

Doobega toh tar jaaega
Har zarra mera
Varna tadap ke hi guzrega
Roz marra mera

Kya maine kabhi kiya hai
Thoda ishq bhi khudse 
Mil jaayega phir jo dhoondta hun 
Main darbadar kabse

Woh sukoon shayad mujhse hi hai
Mujh mein hi tha aur mujh mein hi hai
Woh sukoon shayad mujhse hi hai
Mujh mein hi tha aur mujh mein hi hai

Woh sukoon mujhse hai‚Ä¶
Mujh mein hai sukoon‚Ä¶

Makar Sankranti Katha in Hindi, Secret of Sesame and Jaggery, Makar Sankranti Special Katha 2026, Makar Sankranti story, Makar Sankranti, Makar Sankranti puja, Makar Sankranti story, Makar Sankranti festival, Makar Sankranti story, Makar Sankranti story, Sankranti, Makar Sankranti story, Makar Sankranti video, Makar Sankranti saga, Makar Sankranti fast story, Dharmaraj ji's story, Sankranti story, Makar Sankranti story, Makar Sankranti mythological story, Makar Sankranti story in Hindi

Makar Sankranti is the sacred festival when the Sun God leaves Sagittarius and enters Capricorn. From this day, the Sun's movement shifts northward, which is called Uttarayan. In the scriptures, the Uttarayan period is associated with positive energy, virtue, and salvation.

This festival is celebrated in different states of India under different names, such as Pongal, Uttarayan, Bihu, Khichdi, etc.

üåæ Spiritual Significance of Makar Sankranti

The Sun God is considered the factor of the soul.

Donations made on this day yield manifold benefits.

Sesame seeds remove impurities from the body and mind.

A celebration of welcoming the new harvest.

A message of light and positivity in life.

üôè A brief ritual for Makar Sankranti.

Breathing with holy water in the morning.

Offering water, sesame seeds, and red flowers to the rising sun.

Chanting Surya mantras.

Donating sesame seeds, jaggery, food, and clothes.

Maintaining harmony in the family and society.

üçØ Special Message of Sesame and Jaggery.

Sesame seeds symbolize life's difficulties, and jaggery symbolizes sweetness.

Together, they teach us to maintain sweetness even in difficult circumstances.
